"title": "7340: clean and unclean",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7340: clean and unclean",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The distinction between things which were ritually acceptable and unacceptable to God. Animals were classified as either clean or unclean, denoting their suitability or unsuitability for sacrifice and food. The motives and intentions of the heart were also sometimes judged to be clean or unclean, as uncleanness was often linked with sin.</p>\n<h2>The OT distinction between clean and unclean</h2>\n<h3>The command to distinguish between clean and unclean</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:31\">LEV 15:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:8-Lev10:11\">LEV 10:8–10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:22-Lev20:26\">LEV 20:22–20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:26\">EZK 22:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:23\">EZK 44:23</a></p>\n<h3>The distinction between clean and unclean animals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:2\">GEN 7:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:8-Gen7:9\">GEN 7:8–7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:20\">GEN 8:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:1-Lev11:47\">LEV 11:1–11:47</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:3-Deut14:20\">DEU 14:3–14:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:11-Lev27:13\">LEV 27:11–27:13</a></p>\n<h3>The NT attitude to clean and unclean animals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:14-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:14–7:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:10-Matt15:20\">MAT 15:10–15:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:11-Acts10:15\">ACT 10:11–10:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:5-Acts11:9\">ACT 11:5–11:9</a></p>\n<h3>Places and inanimate objects could be clean or unclean</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:14\">LEV 10:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:12\">LEV 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:11\">LEV 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:32-Lev11:38\">LEV 11:32–11:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:33-Lev14:57\">LEV 14:33–14:57</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:11\">2CH 13:11</a></p>\n<h2>Causes of uncleanness</h2>\n<h3>Physical contact with anything unclean</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:2-Lev5:3\">LEV 5:2–5:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:19\">LEV 7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:3-Hos9:4\">HOS 9:3–9:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:10-Hag2:14\">HAG 2:10–2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Contact with corpses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:11\">NUM 19:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:1-Lev21:4\">LEV 21:1–21:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:10-Lev21:12\">LEV 21:10–21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:5-Num6:8\">NUM 6:5–6:8</a></p>\n<h3>Infectious skin diseases</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:1-Lev13:46\">LEV 13:1–13:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:1-Lev14:32\">LEV 14:1–14:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:2-Matt8:4\">MAT 8:2–8:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:40-Mark1:44\">MRK 1:40–1:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:12-Luke5:14\">LUK 5:12–5:14</a></p>\n<h3>Certain bodily functions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:2\">LEV 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:5\">LEV 12:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:1-Lev15:33\">LEV 15:1–15:33</a></p>\n<h2>Consequences of uncleanness</h2>\n<h3>Exclusion from worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:3-Lev22:5\">LEV 22:3–22:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:4\">LEV 12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:6-Num9:12\">NUM 9:6–9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:24-1Sam20:26\">1SA 20:24–20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:19\">2CH 23:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:17\">2CH 30:17</a></p>\n<h3>Isolation from God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:2\">NUM 5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:20-Lev7:21\">LEV 7:20–7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:10-Deut23:11\">DEU 23:10–23:11</a></p>\n<h2>Cleansing from uncleanness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:29-Lev16:30\">LEV 16:29–16:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:6-Lev12:8\">LEV 12:6–12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:15-Lev16:16\">LEV 16:15–16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:4-Lev22:7\">LEV 22:4–22:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:9-Num6:12\">NUM 6:9–6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:1-Num19:22\">NUM 19:1–19:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:21-Num31:24\">NUM 31:21–31:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:13\">HEB 9:13</a></p>\n<h2>Inner, spiritual cleanness and uncleanness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:9\">JOB 33:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:7\">PSA 51:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:5\">GEN 20:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps24:3-Ps24:4\">PSA 24:3–24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:9\">PRO 20:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:15-Isa1:16\">ISA 1:15–1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:6\">ISA 64:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:8\">LAM 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:25\">EZK 36:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:10-Matt15:20\">MAT 15:10–15:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:14-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:14–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:25-Matt23:28\">MAT 23:25–23:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:28\">ACT 10:28</a></p>",
